qas.question: How many Knights are in The Order?
How many Knights and Dames Commander?
How many commanders are in The Order?
How many officers and members maybe be appointed per year?
Who has the highest numbers of the British Orders of Chivalry?

context: The Order is limited to <a0_0>300 Knights and Dames Grand Cross<a0_0/>, <a1_0>845<a1_0/> Knights and Dames Commander, and <a2_0>8,960<a2_0/> Commanders. There are no limits applied to the total number of members of the fourth and fifth classes, but no more than <a3_0>858 Officers and 1,464 Members<a3_0/> may be appointed per year. Foreign recipients, as honorary members, do not contribute to the numbers restricted to the Order as full members do. Although the <a4_0>Order of the British Empire<a4_0/> has by far the highest number of members of the British Orders of Chivalry, with over 100,000 living members worldwide, there are fewer appointments to knighthoods than in other orders.
